webnn/ort: annotate Environment::Create with its real lock requirement.

Create() calls GetDependentEpPackages(), which is
EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(GetLock()), and is only invoked from
GetOrCreateInstance() under an AutoLock — but Create() itself carried no
annotation, so -Wthread-safety-analysis (an error in the Windows mono
build, where this ORT backend actually compiles) rejects it. Annotating
the declaration states the existing contract; no behavior change.

--- a/services/webnn/ort/environment.h	2026-07-08 22:52:57
+++ b/services/webnn/ort/environment.h	2026-07-08 22:52:57
@@ -112,7 +112,7 @@
  private:
   static base::expected<scoped_refptr<Environment>, std::string> Create(
       const base::flat_map<std::string, mojom::EpPackageInfoPtr>&
-          ep_package_info_map);
+          ep_package_info_map) EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(GetLock());
 
   ~Environment();
 
